<topic id='business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Urgent Treatment Centre - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre">Urgent Treatment Centre</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_department">Emergency Care Department</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre">Urgent Treatment Centres</xref>
  (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre">UTC</xref>) are Community and Primary Care facilities providing access to urgent care for a local population.        </p>
      <p>
All 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre">Urgent Treatment Centres</xref>
 are classed as 
              <xref outputclass="attribute"
               keyref="attribute_emergency_care_department_type">EMERGENCY CARE DEPARTMENT TYPE</xref>
 National Code 
              <i>'Other type of A&amp;E/minor injury 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITY</xref>
 with designated accommodation for the reception of accident and emergency 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>. The department may be doctor led or 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSE</xref>
 led and treats at least minor injuries and illnesses and can be routinely accessed without 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>. A 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
 mainly or entirely 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>
 based (for example a 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>
 or 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_out-patient_clinic">Out-Patient Clinic</xref>) is excluded even though it may treat a number of 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 with minor illness or injury. Excludes NHS walk-in centres'.            </i>
      </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_urgent_treatment_centre">Urgent Treatment Centres</xref>
 see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/urgent-emergency-care/urgent-treatment-centres/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Urgent Treatment Centres.</xref>
      </p>
  </div>
